  "texts": [
    "Zero-shot encoding tests the ability of the model to interpolate (or predict) IFG's unseen brain embeddings from GPT-2's contextual embeddings.",
    "Zero-shot decoding reverses the procedure and tests the ability of the model to interpolate (or predict) unseen contextual embedding of GPT-2 from IFG's brain embeddings.",
    "In the zero-shot encoding analysis, we use the geometry of the embedding space to predict (interpolate) the neural responses of unique words not seen during training.",
    "Specifically, we used nine folds of the data (990 unique words) to learn a linear transformation between the contextual embeddings from GPT-2 and the brain embeddings in IFG.",
    "Next, we used the tenth fold to predict (interpolate) IFG brain embeddings for a new set of 110 unique words to which the encoding model was never exposed."
  ],
